leftColumnFAQs.question: What is the purpose of the Club?
leftColumnFAQs.answer: The Tech Club aims to foster a community of technology enthusiasts, providing resources and opportunities to learn, collaborate, and innovate in various tech domains.

leftColumnFAQs.question: Do I need prior knowledge to join the Club?
leftColumnFAQs.answer: No prior knowledge is required! We welcome members at all skill levels, from beginners to advanced tech enthusiasts.

leftColumnFAQs.question: What activities does the Club organize?
leftColumnFAQs.answer: We organize workshops, hackathons, coding challenges, guest lectures, and collaborative projects in various areas like AI, web development, cybersecurity, and more.

leftColumnFAQs.question: Are there any membership fees for joining?
leftColumnFAQs.answer: Membership is free! You can participate in most events without any cost. However, some special events may have minimal fees.

leftColumnFAQs.question: Will there be opportunities for hands-on learning?
leftColumnFAQs.answer: Yes, we emphasize practical, hands-on learning experiences, from coding sessions to real-world project collaborations and hackathons.

leftColumnFAQs.question: Can I get guidance or mentorship in the club?
leftColumnFAQs.answer: Absolutely! Our club members and mentors are always ready to help. You'll also have access to industry experts during special events and workshops.

rightColumnFAQs.question: What should I bring for the hackathon?
rightColumnFAQs.answer: Bring your student ID, laptops, gadgets, or anything else you want to work on.

rightColumnFAQs.question: Will the hackathon have Wi-Fi facilities?
rightColumnFAQs.answer: Yes, we will provide Wi-Fi throughout the event.

rightColumnFAQs.question: Can I participate without a team?
rightColumnFAQs.answer: No, this hackathon is a team event. You can team up with others in our community group.

rightColumnFAQs.question: Will you sponsor our travel costs?
rightColumnFAQs.answer: No, we do not reimburse travel costs, but accommodation is provided for those traveling from outside the city.

rightColumnFAQs.question: Will there be any mentoring sessions?
rightColumnFAQs.answer: Yes, mentors will guide you throughout the hackathon.

rightColumnFAQs.question: Do I need to be a student to participate?
rightColumnFAQs.answer: Yes, this hackathon is open to high school and undergraduate students.
